`combineLatest` emits whenever any source emits, using the latest value from each. `zip` waits until every source has emitted a NEW value, then emits them as an index-aligned tuple. Use `zip` when emissions are index-matched pairs (e.g., request id N with response id N).

```typescript
import { Observable, zip } from "rxjs";
import { map } from "rxjs/operators";

interface Request { id: number; url: string; }
interface Response { id: number; status: number; body: string; }

interface Pair {
  request: Request;
  response: Response;
}

declare const request$: Observable<Request>;
declare const response$: Observable<Response>;

export const pairs$: Observable<Pair> = zip(request$, response$).pipe(
  map(([request, response]: [Request, Response]): Pair => ({ request, response }))
);
```

